Police have arrested a 19-year-old youth in Paarl after a teenager was hit on the head with a stone. CAPE TOWN - Police have arrested a 19-year-old youth in Paarl after a teenager was hit on the head with a stone.The incident occurred near Paarlzicht Primary School on Wednesday.The 17-year-old victim died shortly after being hit over the head with a stone.The police s Frederick Van Wyk says two others have since been released from custody, in connection with the crime. Three suspects aged between 17 and 19 on the charge of murder. Two suspects were later released after a thorough investigation by the detectives. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)